###

#####
Beta-lactams
#####

.idpenicillin
Antibiotic: Penicillin
Indication: 
Duration: 
Dosing: 
Route:
Administration precautions: caution if patient had prior reaction to beta-lactam antibiotic
Allergies: diarrhea, skin rash
Rare Toxicities: (Heme: anemia, thrombocytopenia, neutropenia, agranulocytosis; CNS: seizure; 

CNS:  seizures

Renal:  nephrotoxicity, interstitial nephritis

Hepatic:  transient increases in transaminases

Other:  Jarisch-Herxheimer Reaction (fever, chills, sweating, tachycardia, hyperventilation, flushing, and myalgia)
Lab surveillance: CBC, urinalysis, BUN, SCr, AST and ALT

