.idzosyn
Antibiotic: Zosyn (piperacillin-tazobactam)
Indication: 
Duration: 
Dosing: 
Route: IV (over 30 minutes or with an extended infusion to maximize time above MIC)
Administration precautions: 
Toxicities:
- most common adverse reactions (incidence >5%) are diarrhea,
constipation, nausea, headache and insomnia
- with vancomycin may increase the
incidence of acute kidney injury
- can significantly reduce tobramycin concentrations in hemodialysis patients
Lab surveillance: 

